{"word":"Abdon","slug":"abdon","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Abdon</b> <a href=\"#/H5658\">H5658</a> <br/> 1. A judge of Israel, in the time of the judges<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=12&verse=15'>Jdg 12:15</a><br/> 2. A Levitical city<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=21&verse=30'>Jos 21:30</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=6&verse=74'>1Ch 6:74</a><br/> 3. A Benjamite chief<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=8&verse=23'>1Ch 8:23</a><br/><a href='S:Achbor'>Achbor</a><br/> 4. Son of Gibeon<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=8&verse=30'>1Ch 8:30</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=9&verse=36'>1Ch 9:36</a><br/> 5. Son of Micah, called Achbor<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=34&verse=20'>2Ch 34:20</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=22&verse=12'>2Ki 22:12</a>"}]}